news.title: China: CIFI Holdings expects to swing to a loss for 2022
news.para: The Shanghai-based company expects to post a core net loss of between 5.10 billion yuan ($734 million) and 5.60 billion yuan for the year ended Dec. 31, 2022, compared to a profit of 7.28 billion yuan recorded a year earlier.

news.title: Accused knew of all circumstances that led to Chintels Paradiso collapse, says CBI chargesheet
news.para: They allegedly not only overlooked the circumstances but Austin, in a bid to escape from the liability, also managed to get two backdated agreements of repair from an Amroha-based labour contractor, reveals the chargesheet filed by CBI’s special crime branch (SCB) in the court of CBI special magistrate Vinod Kumar last week.

news.title: Gujarat government collected Rs 1,606 crore from construction cess in three years
news.para: The government said that in the financial year 2020-21, the cess collection was Rs 452.92 crore. This rose to Rs 572.24 crore in 2021-22, an increase of 26.34%.

news.title: Patna civic body organises camps for holding tax collection
news.para: The PMC deployed teams in Sector-A of all the wards on Friday for the convenience of the residents. Each sector will host the camp for two days.

news.title: Lucknow civic body to collect property tax on weekends
news.para: Chief taxation officer, LMC, Ashok Singh said, “The civic body has collected Rs 273.15 crore as property tax till March 10 in this financial year. The civic body had collected around Rs 250 crore during the same period in the last financial year. "

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 14,000 properties over tax default
news.para: The tax and revenue department sealed 4,565 properties in the east zone, 2,605 properties in the west zone, 2,110 properties in the south zone and 1,600 properties in the south west zone.

news.title: Punjab: Nod to mining policy to provide sand-gravel at affordable prices
news.para: Now, the mining sites have been divided into two categories - commercial mining sites (CMS) and public mining sites (PMS).

news.title: Over 500 cases of illegal sand mining registered in Madhya Pradesh
news.para: The district wise reply stated overall 52 cases of illegal sand mining and 536 cases of illegal sand transportation in MP during the period of 11 months.

news.title: Guwahati civic body yet to recover Rs 100 crore property tax
news.para: The civic body has collected Rs 104 crore revenue as property tax till Friday since the drive was started. The civic body had initially given a 50% waiver to those who had not paid property tax for a long time.

news.title: Rovers to aid in clearing land survey applications in Maharashtra
news.para: On Thursday, deputy chief minister and state finance minister Devendra Fadnavis said during his budget speech that rover machines would be used to speed up measurement and clear land survey applications within 90 days.

news.title: Panvel civic body seals 118 commercial shops over non-payment of property tax dues
news.para: ​Subsequently, several commercial property owners have immediately cleared the outstanding amount of property tax to prevent the sealing of their property and to avoid loss of business.

news.title: Jaipur development body demolishes three illegal colonies in separate zones
news.para: “All these colonies were coming up illegally by converting agricultural land. We have zero tolerance policy against any illegal colony in the city. So, we had demolished all these three upcoming colonies,” said Raghuveer Saini, chief of the enforcement branch of JDA.

news.title: Bill for mandatory CCTV cameras in public spaces introduced in Assam assembly
news.para: The owners of such spaces have to install the surveillance equipment within a stipulated period, failing which the premise may be sealed by local authorities, as per the proposed legislation.

news.title: Maharashtra co-operation department against repealing MOFA, cites benefits for stand
news.para: The state housing department, headed by deputy chief minister Devendra Fadnavis, had sought the cooperation department’s opinion on repealing MOFA as well as to review the draft of the new Maharashtra Transfer of Title in Real Estate Project bill, which is to replace MOFA.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to organise camps at housing complexes for mutation of flats
news.para: The KMC brass has taken the decision following requests from flat owners across the city who face harassment while trying to do mutation of their properties.
